},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":1},"end":{"line":60,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Complaints received by UCAR will be handled pursuant to the procedures outlined in ","position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":1},"end":{"line":60,"column":1}},"key":"D4oI7Y4o2m"},{"type":"link","url":"https://sundog.ucar.edu/Interact/Pages/Content/Document.aspx?id=5140","position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":1},"end":{"line":60,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"UCAR’s Complaint and Investigations Procedures","position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":1},"end":{"line":60,"column":1}},"key":"aF7qIUfBBD"}],"urlSource":"https://sundog.ucar.edu/Interact/Pages/Content/Document.aspx?id=5140","key":"XpV46B06Vj"},{"type":"text","value":". Complaints to UCAR will be held as confidential as practicable under the circumstances, and retaliation against a person who initiates a complaint or an inquiry about inappropriate behavior will not be tolerated.","position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":1},"end":{"line":60,"column":1}},"key":"jFkkQMCFay"}],"key":"KVVPvvFPu8"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":62,"column":1},"end":{"line":62,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you require a reasonable accommodation due to a disability or for assistance as an individual with Limited English Proficiency (LEP), please contact UCAR’s ","position":{"start":{"line":62,"column":1},"end":{"line":62,"column":1}},"key":"ZkumXJZvFN"},{"type":"link","url":"chro@ucar.edu","position":{"start":{"line":62,"column":1},"end":{"line":62,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Chief Human Resources Officer","position":{"start":{"line":62,"column":1},"end":{"line":62,"column":1}},"key":"l8gWOKv8ut"}],"urlSource":"chro@ucar.edu","key":"Pwysc4xEFu"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":62,"column":1},"end":{"line":62,"column":1}},"key":"bcnX8cUV94"}],"key":"cdOxKqthCn"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":64,"column":1},"end":{"line":64,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Any Contributor can use these reporting methods even if they are not directly affiliated with UCAR. The Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) page for reporting is ","position":{"start":{"line":64,"column":1},"end":{"line":64,"column":1}},"key":"FuInhHDmOC"},{"type":"link","url":"https://www.ucar.edu/who-we-are/ethics","position":{"start":{"line":64,"column":1},"end":{"line":64,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"here","position":{"start":{"line":64,"column":1},"end":{"line":64,"column":1}},"key":"tnEmyqZTAV"}],"urlSource":"https://www.ucar.edu/who-we-are/ethics","key":"krusmyKciM"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":64,"column":1},"end":{"line":64,"column":1}},"key":"GHe8Vhzbk4"}],"key":"tCr3hXKcAT"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1},"end":{"line":66,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Confidentiality","position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1},"end":{"line":66,"column":1}},"key":"SkMxeEAO0R"}],"identifier":"confidentiality","label":"Confidentiality","html_id":"confidentiality","implicit":true,"key":"iQJHn8FXlg"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":67,"column":1},"end":{"line":67,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":67,"column":1},"end":{"line":67,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"All reports will be kept confidential","position":{"start":{"line":67,"column":1},"end":{"line":67,"column":1}},"key":"rqhUs0QMhp"}],"key":"v8sOlgmbL4"},{"type":"text","value":". When we discuss incidents with people who are reported, we will anonymize details as much as we can to protect reporter privacy.","position":{"start":{"line":67,"column":1},"end":{"line":67,"column":1}},"key":"bmuF9jbqdf"}],"key":"HMjiy61dqa"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"However, some incidents happen in one-on-one interactions, and even if the details are anonymized, the reported person may be able to guess who made the report. If you have concerns about retaliation or your safety, please note those in your report. We still encourage you to report so that we can support you while keeping our community members safe. In some cases, we can compile several anonymized reports into a pattern of behavior and take action on that pattern.","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"key":"yVyXPJjp4I"}],"key":"V3JtKHiCWJ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":71,"column":1},"end":{"line":71,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If a public statement is necessary, the identities of all individuals involved will remain confidential unless those individuals instruct us otherwise.","position":{"start":{"line":71,"column":1},"end":{"line":71,"column":1}},"key":"iFqRd8p7vG"}],"key":"MzHwXrJQ0T"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":73,"column":1},"end":{"line":73,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Conflicts of Interest","position":{"start":{"line":73,"column":1},"end":{"line":73,"column":1}},"key":"MKDNTrF8rS"}],"identifier":"conflicts-of-interest","label":"Conflicts of Interest","html_id":"conflicts-of-interest","implicit":true,"key":"wf6snIJMc3"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If a member of the project administrators has a conflict of interest regarding a report, they will recuse themselves from discussing and handling the incident. They will not have access to the incident documentation, and they will excuse themselves from any conversations involving handling the incident.","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"key":"xffNlVkE4i"}],"key":"Q6uL04D1Rf"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":77,"column":1},"end":{"line":77,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Consequences","position":{"start":{"line":77,"column":1},"end":{"line":77,"column":1}},"key":"x2rPu8Zc2o"}],"identifier":"consequences","label":"Consequences","html_id":"consequences","implicit":true,"key":"obPISb545c"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":79,"column":1},"end":{"line":79,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Upon receipt of a complaint, the project administrator(s) may take any action deemed necessary and appropriate under the circumstances. Such action can include things such as: removing, editing, or rejecting comments, commits, code, wiki edits, email, issues, and other contributions that are not aligned to this Code of Conduct, or banning temporarily or permanently any contributor for other behaviors that are deemed inappropriate, threatening, offensive, or harmful. Project administrators also have the right to report violations to UCAR HR as well as to a contributor’s home institution and/or law enforcement. In the event an incident is reported to UCAR, UCAR will follow its Complaint and Investigations Procedure.","position":{"start":{"line":79,"column":1},"end":{"line":79,"column":1}},"key":"rRbKE71iTn"}],"key":"IN66AKz1lp"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Process for Changes","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"key":"Okjrz6E3Pe"}],"identifier":"process-for-changes","label":"Process for Changes","html_id":"process-for-changes","implicit":true,"key":"mKLUmdoy6I"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":83,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"All UCAR managed projects are required to adopt this Contributor Code of Conduct. Adoption is assumed even if not expressly stated in the repository. Projects should fill in sections where prompted with project-specific information, including, project name and adoption date.","position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":83,"column":1}},"key":"g4bMKP4d8I"}],"key":"Fmh9EZactZ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":85,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Projects that adopt this Code of Conduct need to stay up to date with UCAR’s Contributor Code of Conduct, linked with a DOI in the Attribution section below. Projects can make limited substantive changes to the Code of Conduct, however, the changes must be limited in scope and may not contradict the UCAR Contributor Code of Conduct.","position":{"start":{"line":85,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"key":"bQuDTNeUcy"}],"key":"rpqOLDSGab"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":87,"column":1},"end":{"line":87,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Attribution","position":{"start":{"line":87,"column":1},"end":{"line":87,"column":1}},"key":"cqVxsC1IND"}],"identifier":"attribution","label":"Attribution","html_id":"attribution","implicit":true,"key":"U44aP5dkFi"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This Code of Conduct was originally adapted from the ","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"key":"LCeA9ycA44"},{"type":"link","url":"http://contributor-covenant.org/version/1/4","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Contributor Covenant","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"key":"fqz68e0fAp"}],"urlSource":"http://contributor-covenant.org/version/1/4","key":"K2VA9Rdtdx"},{"type":"text","value":", version 1.4. We then aligned it with the UCAR Participant Code of Conduct, which also borrows from the American Geophysical Union (AGU) Code of Conduct. The UCAR Participant Code of Conduct applies to both UCAR employees as well as participants in activities run by UCAR. The original version of this for all software projects that have strong management from UCAR or UCAR staff is available on the UCAR website at ","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"key":"dSRqW8zjeA"},{"type":"cite","url":"https://doi.org/10.5065/6w2c-a132","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"University Corporation for Atmospheric Research Office of General Counsel (2019)","key":"bhef8ndF5F"}],"kind":"narrative","label":"https://doi.org/10.5065/6w2c-a132","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.5065/6w2c-a132","enumerator":"1","key":"rblWMS7Z1h"},{"type":"text","value":". The date that it was adopted by this project was September 11, 2023. When responding to complaints, UCAR HR will do so based on the latest published version. Therefore, any project-specific changes should follow the Process for Changes section above.","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"key":"iUzj86tsH0"}],"key":"pwU3ceBMSD"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer and recipient of federal funds, UCAR complies with Title VI, Title VII, and Title IX of the Civil Rights Act; the Rehabilitation Act of 1973, as amended, and the Age Discrimination in Employment Act of 1975, as amended. See ","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"key":"RXyZ9PXRTE"},{"type":"link","url":"https://www.ucar.edu/who-we-are/ethics-integrity/nondiscrimination","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"UCAR’s Nondiscrimination Statement","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"key":"FfoS9K5S8b"}],"urlSource":"https://www.ucar.edu/who-we-are/ethics-integrity/nondiscrimination","key":"MeQhHKuWv1"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"key":"l9bG4zcVdp"}],"key":"YW9E221FEs"}],"key":"fD4irgBXjY"}],"key":"YoBiGJulOS"},"references":{"cite":{"order":["https://doi.org/10.5065/6w2c-a132"],"data":{"https://doi.org/10.5065/6w2c-a132":{"label":"https://doi.org/10.5065/6w2c-a132","enumerator":"1","doi":"10.5065/6W2C-A132","html":"University Corporation for Atmospheric Research Office of General Counsel. (2019). <i>UCAR Contributor Code of Conduct</i>. <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"https://doi.org/10.5065/6W2C-A132\">10.5065/6W2C-A132</a>","url":"https://doi.org/10.5065/6W2C-A132"}}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"Metrics","url":"/metrics","group":"2023"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3000"}